---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout 
  title="About Echo Stories - Independent Film Production Prague"
  description="Prague-based independent film production company founded by Iuliia Mamaeva. We develop author-driven fiction and documentary films from Europe, Central Asia, and the Middle East."
  type="website"
>
  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-6 py-12 md:py-16">
    <h1 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-medium mb-8">About</h1>

    <div class="space-y-6 text-base md:text-lg leading-relaxed">
      <p>
        <strong>Echo Stories</strong> is a Prague-based independent film production company founded by producer
        <strong>Iuliia Mamaeva</strong>, specializing in author-driven fiction and documentary films.
        We connect European talent with filmmakers from Central Asia and the Middle East,
        building a slate defined by international collaboration and cross-regional storytelling.
      </p>

      <p>
        Our mission is to amplify unique voices and untold stories from diverse cultural backgrounds,
        creating films that resonate across borders. We focus on creative, author-driven projects
        that challenge conventional narratives and offer fresh perspectives on contemporary issues.
      </p>
      
      <p>
        Although recently established, the company has quickly gained recognition in the international
        film community, participating in major development platforms including the
        <strong>MIDPOINT Series Launch/Short</strong>, <strong>Be2Be Exchange at MIA</strong>,
        <strong>East-West Talent Lab</strong>, and the <strong>ECAM Forum</strong>.
      </p>
      
      <p>
        Currently in development is the debut feature film of director Liza Chakanova,
        <em>"Kupala Night"</em>, which won the Belarusian Filmmakers' Network development incubator
        program and was presented at the <strong>Berlinale – BIFA Pitching Event 2026</strong>.
        The company's short animation <em>"Nun"</em> has been selected for the
        <strong>Zlín Film Festival</strong>, <strong>Anifilm 2026</strong> and the
        <strong>Cannes Short Film Corner | Rendez-vous Industry</strong>.
        The comedy mockumentary series <em>"Paralegal"</em> is set to pitch at the
        <strong>Writers' Vision Pitch @ Seriencamp Festival 2026</strong>.
      </p>
    </div>
    
    <div class="mt-16">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-medium mb-6">Selected Projects</h2>
      <div class="space-y-3 text-base">
        <div>
          <span class="font-medium">Completed:</span>
          <span class="ml-2 text-gray-600">Nun (short animation) — Zlín Film Festival, Anifilm 2026, Cannes Short Film Corner</span>
        </div>
        <div>
          <span class="font-medium">Pre-production:</span>
          <span class="ml-2 text-gray-600">Night Games (short)</span>
        </div>
        <div>
          <span class="font-medium">Post-production:</span>
          <span class="ml-2 text-gray-600">The Apple Tree That Blossomed Twice (short)</span>
        </div>
        <div>
          <span class="font-medium">In Development:</span>
          <span class="ml-2 text-gray-600">Kupala Night (feature), Paralegal (comedy mockumentary series) — Writers' Vision Pitch @ Seriencamp Festival 2026</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</Layout>
